='''6'''\n| RD3-team02={{Flagicon|CAN}} [[Frank Jonik]]\n| RD3-score02=3\n| RD3-team03={{Flagicon|CAN}} '''[[Jim Wych]]'''\n| RD3-score03='''6'''\n| RD3-team04={{Flagicon|CAN}} [[Kirk Stevens]]\n| RD3-score04=2\n\n| RD4-team01={{Flagicon|CAN}} '''[[Cliff Thorburn]]'''\n| RD4-score01='''6'''\n| RD4-team02={{Flagicon|CAN}} [[Jim Wych]]\n| RD4-score02=2\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Snooker season 1986/1987}}\n\n[[Category:1986 in snooker]]\n[[Category:1986 in Canadian sports]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Individual Snooker Tournament\n|tournament_name=Canadian Professional Championship\n|logo=\n|dates=August 1986\n|venue=Snooker Centre\n|location=[[Toronto]]\n|country=[[Canada]]\n|organisation=\n|format=Non-[[Snooker world rankings|ranking]] event\n|Total prize fund=\u00a313,000\n|winners_share=\u00a32,900\n|highest_break=129 ([[Jim Wych]])\n|winner={{flagicon|CAN}} [[Cliff Thorburn]]\n|runner_up={{flagicon|CAN}} [[Jim Wych]]\n|score=6\u20132\n|previous=[[1985 Canadian Professional Championship|1985]]\n|next=[[1987 Canadian Professional Championship|1987]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1986 [[Canadian Professional Championship]]''' was a professional non-ranking [[snooker]] tournament, which took place in August 1986 at Snooker Centre, [[Toronto]], [[Canada]].<ref>{{citeweb|title=Other National Professional Championship|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120107161810/http://www.cajt.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/natpro.html|publisher=Chris Turner's Snooker Archive|accessdate=20 February 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"SCENE\" />\n\n[[Cliff Thorburn]] won the title for the third year in a row, and fourth overall, by beating [[Jim Wych]] 6\u20132 in the final.<ref name=\"Cuesport\">{{cite book|last=Hayton|first=Eric|title=Cuesport Book of Professional Snooker|page=154}}</ref> Wych compiled the highest break of the tournament, 129, in his quarter-final match against Bernie Mikkelsen.<ref name=\"SCENE\" />\n\nThe [[World Professional Billiards and Snooker Association]] funded \u00a313,000 in prize money through its national championship subsidy, a scheme which provided \u00a31,000 per entrant. Thorburn received \u00a32,900 as winner.<ref name=\"SCENE\">{{cite magazine |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Thorburn wins Canadian title \u2026 and Francisco takes South African  |magazine=Snooker Scene |page=14-15 |publisher=Everton's News Agency |issue=September 1986 }}</ref>\n\n==Main draw==\n<ref>{{cite web|title=1986 Canadian Professional Championship Results Grid|url=http://www.snookerdatabase.co.uk/EventResultGrid.aspx?EventKey=622|publisher=Snooker Database|accessdate=20 February 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"SCENE\" /><ref name=\"87HALE\">{{cite book |last=Hale |first=Janice |date=1987 |title=Rothmans Snooker Yearbook 1987-88  |location=Aylesbury |publisher=Queen Anne Press |page=273 |isbn=0356146901 }}</ref> \n{{16TeamBracket-Compact-NoSeeds-Byes\n| RD1=First round<br/>Best of 11 frames\n| RD2=Quarter-finals<br/>Best of 11 frames\n| RD3=Semi-finals<br/>Best of 11 frames\n| RD4=Final<br/>Best of 11 frames\n\n| RD1-team03={{Flagicon|CAN}} '''[[Gerry Watson]]'''\n| RD1-score03='''6'''\n| RD1-team04={{Flagicon|CAN}} [[Joe Cagianello]]\n| RD1-score04=3\n| RD1-team05={{Flagicon|CAN}} '''[[Frank Jonik]]'''\n| RD1-score05='''6'''\n| RD1-team06={{Flagicon|CAN}} [[Gino Rigitano]]\n| RD1-score06=1\n| RD1-team07={{Flagicon|CAN}} '''[[Bob Chaperon]]'''\n| RD1-score07='''6'''\n| RD1-team08={{Flagicon|CAN}} [[Jim Bear]]\n| RD1-score08=3\n| RD1-team11={{Flagicon|CAN}} '''[[Bernie Mikkelsen]]'''\n| RD1-score11='''6'''\n| RD1-team12={{Flagicon|CAN}} [[Wayne Sanderson]]\n| RD1-score12=1\n| RD1-team15={{Flagicon|CAN}} '''[[Paul Thornley]]'''\n| RD1-score15='''6'''\n| RD1-team16={{Flagicon|CAN}} [[Mario Morra (snooker player)|Mario Morra]]\n| RD1-score16=4\n\n| RD2-team01={{Flagicon|CAN}} '''[[Cliff Thorburn]]'''\n| RD2-score01='''6'''\n| RD2-team02={{Flagicon|CAN}} [[Gerry Watson]]\n| RD2-score02=1\n| RD2-team03={{Flagicon|CAN}} '''[[Frank Jonik]]'''\n| RD2-score03